# Flask Program

```python
from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route("/")
def home():
    return "<h1>Welcome to AI Employee Salary Predictor</h1>"

if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run(debug=True)
```

---

# Program Explanation

## Import Flask

```python
from flask import Flask
```

Imports the Flask framework.

---

## Create Flask Application

```python
app = Flask(__name__)
```

Creates a Flask application object.

---

## Create Route

```python
@app.route("/")
```

Maps the Home URL (`/`) to the `home()` function.

---

## Create Function

```python
def home():
```

Executes when the Home page is requested.

---

## Return Response

```python
return "<h1>Welcome to AI Employee Salary Predictor</h1>"
```

Returns an HTML response to the browser.

---

## Run Server

```python
app.run(debug=True)
```

Starts the Flask Development Server.

---

