# Interview Questions

### What is Flask?

Flask is a lightweight Python web framework used to build web applications and APIs.

---

### What is Werkzeug?

Werkzeug is the WSGI utility library used internally by Flask.

---

### What is app.py?

The main Python file that starts the Flask application.

---

### What is @app.route("/")?

It maps the Home URL to a Python function.

---

### What is debug=True?

It automatically reloads the application after code changes and shows detailed errors.

---

### Why do we use a Virtual Environment?

To isolate project dependencies and avoid conflicts with the system Python.

